<item>
            <title>[LU-11088] ll_opcode2str() must handle invalid opcodes safely</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11088</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There are at least two places where &lt;tt&gt;ll_opcode2str()&lt;/tt&gt; is passed an opcode from the wire. If that opcode is unknown the &lt;tt&gt;opcode_offset()&lt;/tt&gt; will return &lt;tt&gt;(u32)-1&lt;/tt&gt; and one of the assertions in &lt;tt&gt;ll_opcode2str()&lt;/tt&gt; will fail.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="52556">LU-11088</key>
